\nscenario is presented; after the preequilibrium emission ceases in the\ncomposite system, cold light fragments are formed in a hotter gas of nucleons\nand stay cold until the composite system underdoes multifragmentation. For\nreaction with 197Au at 47A MeV a significant radial expansion takes place. For\nreactions with 58Ni and 92Mo at 47A MeV semi-transparency becomes prominent.\nThe differing reaction dynamics drastically change the kinematic\ncharacteristics of emitted fragments. This scenario gives consistent\nexplanations for many existing experimental results in the Fermi energy domain.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 27 Aug 2003 16:08:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2011-07-19"}
